Sentencas: Anode current collection points (ACCPs) were fabricated on the outside surface of a tubular anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Anode Current Collecting Efficiency of Tubular Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The ACCPs were distributed axially along the SOFC tube with the distance between every adjacent two ACCPs the same.
Titulo: Anode Current Collecting Efficiency of Tubular Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effect of collecting current with different number of ACCPs on the performance of the SOFC was studied.
Titulo: Anode Current Collecting Efficiency of Tubular Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It was found that with the same effective area, using more ACCPs to collect the current leads to better perfor-mance, while with a SOFC with a determined total surface area, there is an optimum number of ACCPs to be made and used considering the area occupied by the ACCPs themselves.
Titulo: Anode Current Collecting Efficiency of Tubular Anode-supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
